<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4131E9356B9DD7B4FDC5205A" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574131E9356B9DD7B4FDC5205A" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,1331]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356B9DD7B4FE912392" bold="true" box="[199,326,476,500]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named in accordance with the strongly suspected host plant, 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356FC0D7B5FAF62392" box="[1178,1313,477,500]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356FC0D7B5FAF62392" box="[1178,1313,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Latin noun peuce is derived from the Ancient Greek noun η πƐύκη meaning spruce or pine, and mainly referring to mountain pines (
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64131E9356A0BD44CFDD2205A" author="Le Maitre, D. C." box="[337,517,548,572]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="407 - 431" refId="ref69382" refString="Le Maitre, D. C. (1998) Pines in cultivation: a global view. In: Richardson, D. M. (ed.) Ecology and Biogeography of Pinus. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York, Melbourne and Madrid, pp. 407 - 431 [paperback edition, 2000]." type="journal article" year="1998">Le Maitre 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4131E9356B9DD423FD6020E1" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574131E9356B9DD423FDB32004" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,1331]" box="[199,612,586,611]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356B9DD423FE932005" bold="true" box="[199,324,587,611]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<collectingRegion id="38082FB54131E9356B9DD423FF282005" box="[199,255,587,611]" country="Afghanistan" name="Khost" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Host</collectingRegion>
plant
</emphasis>
. 
<superScript id="0DB94C1F4131E9356A08D422FE8C2034" attach="right" box="[338,347,586,594]" fontSize="6" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ο</superScript>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356A01D423FDB32004" authority="Grisebach." box="[347,612,586,610]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356A01D423FE332004" box="[347,484,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus peuce</emphasis>
Grisebach.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574131E9356B9DD406FD6020E1" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,1331]" box="[199,695,622,647]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356B9DD406FE3020E1" bold="true" box="[199,487,622,647]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356AAFD407FD8220E1" box="[501,597,623,647]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24131E935693FD407FD7E20E1" box="[613,681,623,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1012,1035]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,333,982]" captionTargetId="figure-496@18.[151,1436,333,990]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8. Records of Xyela alpigena (51 specimens from 22 collection sites) and X. peuce (21 specimens from 5 collection sites) and natural distribution of the (supposed) host plants, Pinus cembra (solid line) and P.peuce (dashed line, both according to Willis et al. 1998)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261338/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4131E9356B9DD4FBFC452754" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574131E9356B9DD4FBFB4121C1" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,1331]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356B9DD4FBFEE320CD" bold="true" box="[199,308,659,683]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356A19D4FBFE1B20CC" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[323,460,659,683]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356A19D4FBFE1B20CC" box="[323,460,659,683]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Xyela peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to the allopatric 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E935681AD4FBFC1420CD" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[832,963,659,683]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E935681AD4FBFC1420CD" box="[832,963,659,683]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356F65D4FBFB7620CC" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[1087,1185,659,682]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356F65D4FBFB7620CC" box="[1087,1185,659,682]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a comparatively longer valviceps than males of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356AABD4D0FDA620A9" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[497,625,695,719]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356AABD4D0FDA620A9" box="[497,625,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(relative length: width of valviceps 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356F53D4DFFB4220A9" box="[1033,1173,695,719]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0005" metricValueMax="4.0894" metricValueMin="3.9116" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="1.575" valueMax="1.61" valueMin="1.54">1.54–1.61 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356FC6D4D0FB2B20A9" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[1180,1276,696,719]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356FC6D4D0FB2B20A9" box="[1180,1276,696,719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356E4AD4DFFA4B20A9" box="[1296,1436,695,719]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7338" metricValueMax="3.8608" metricValueMin="3.6068" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="1.47" valueMax="1.52" valueMin="1.42">1.42–1.52 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356BCDD4B3FEC02095" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,279,731,755]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356BCDD4B3FEC02095" box="[151,279,731,755]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the medial lobe bears fewer cone-like sensilla (14–15 / 22–30). Most females can be identified by the relative length of valvifer 2: valvula 3 ([1.90–]1.95–2.20 / 1.75–1.95). Females of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356FDCD568FB3E2171" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[1158,1257,768,791]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356FDCD568FB3E2171" box="[1158,1257,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are on average paler: only ca 75 % have the kidney-shaped spots separated in front from the black stripe of the frontal furrow by yellow, whereas only ca 25 % of such pale specimens occur among females of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356F58D520FB542139" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[1026,1155,839,863]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356F58D520FB542139" box="[1026,1155,839,863]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other Palearctic species of the 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356BBED503FE9121E5" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[228,326,875,899]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356BBED503FE9121E5" box="[228,326,875,899]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group have either the wings clear (
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E93569BFD503FCAD21E5" authorityName="Sieb. &amp; Zucc. (Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1965" box="[741,890,875,899]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koraiensis">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E93569BFD503FCAD21E5" box="[741,890,875,899]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. koraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E93568D1D503FBFE21E4" authorityName=", Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1965" box="[907,1065,875,898]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E93568D1D503FBFE21E4" box="[907,1065,875,898]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), an evidently longer ovipositor sheath (
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356BB5D5F8FEA721C1" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[239,368,911,935]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricae">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356BB5D5F8FEA721C1" box="[239,368,911,935]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. sibiricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or a different relative length of valvifer 2: valvula 2 (
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356885D5F8FB5221C1" authorityName=", Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1965" box="[991,1157,911,935]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamtshatica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356885D5F8FB5221C1" box="[991,1157,911,935]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. kamtshatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574131E9356B9DD5DBFC452754" blockId="25.[151,1436,151,1331]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64131E9356B9DD5DBFEB321AC" author="Taeger, A." box="[199,356,946,971]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref71876" refString="Taeger, A. (1987) Erganzungen zur Blattwespenfauna Bulgariens und Bearbeitung der Gattung Monostegia O. Costa (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Tenthredinidae). Faunistische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 15 (1), 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1987">Taeger (1987)</bibRefCitation>
first recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356995D5DAFCF821AC" box="[719,815,946,970]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
under the name 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E93568B0D5DBFBBB21AD" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[1002,1132,947,971]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E93568B0D5DBFBBB21AD" box="[1002,1132,947,971]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A female was collected at the edge of snow patches at 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356A84D5BFFDEB2188" box="[478,572,983,1007]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="2050.0">2,050 m</quantity>
altitude. At the collection sites in the Pirin and Rila Mountains in southern 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356BCDD592FF2D2674" box="[151,250,1018,1042]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356A52D593FE432674" box="[264,404,1019,1042]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356A52D593FE432674" box="[264,404,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only representative of the 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356842D593FC8F2674" box="[792,856,1019,1042]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356842D593FC8F2674" box="[792,856,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(‘ 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E935682FD593FC1F2675" box="[885,968,1019,1043]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Strobus</emphasis>
’) group. This presumed Tertiary relic is endemic to the southern Balkans, where it grows in a few places in 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E93568EDD277FBE12651" box="[951,1078,1055,1079]" name="Macedonia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356F1FD277FB772651" box="[1093,1184,1055,1079]" name="Albania" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Albania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356FF5D277FAD82651" box="[1199,1295,1055,1079]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C74131E9356E17D277FA4B2651" box="[1357,1436,1055,1079]" name="Greece" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Greece</collectingCountry>
between 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356A5BD22AFE4C263C" box="[257,411,1090,1114]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="1450.0" valueMax="2100.0" valueMin="800.0">800–2,100 m</quantity>
and forms pure stands above 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356854D22AFCA7263C" box="[782,880,1090,1114]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="1700.0">1,700 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64131E93568DFD22AFBC4263C" author="Mirov, N. T." box="[901,1043,1090,1114]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref69989" refString="Mirov, N. T. (1967) The genus Pinus. The Ronald Press Company, New York, 602 pp." type="book" year="1967">Mirov 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA64131E9356F7FD22AFAB9263C" author="Richardson, D. M. &amp; Rundel, P. W." box="[1061,1390,1090,1114]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="3 - 46" refId="ref70667" refString="Richardson, D. M. &amp; Rundel, P. W. (1998) Ecology and biogeography of Pinus: an introduction. In: Richardson, D. M. (ed.) Ecology and Biogeography of Pinus. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York, Melbourne and Madrid, pp. 3 - 46 [paperback edition, 2000]." type="journal article" year="1998">Richardson &amp; Rundel 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<specimenCount id="ECCA2ADE4131E9356EDAD22AFEDB2619" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="generic">17 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356A6FD200FE402619" box="[309,407,1128,1151]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356A6FD200FE402619" box="[309,407,1128,1151]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected between 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E93569EFD20FFCB52618" box="[693,866,1127,1151]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.025" metricValueMax="2.185" metricValueMin="1.8649999999999998" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="2025.0" valueMax="2185.0" valueMin="1865.0">
<geoCoordinate id="9FF887904131E93569EFD20FFD252619" box="[693,754,1127,1151]" degrees="1,865" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" precision="55" value="1.865">1,865</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="9FF887904131E93569A8D20FFC962619" box="[754,833,1127,1151]" degrees="2,185" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" precision="55" value="-2.185">–2,185</geoCoordinate>
m
</quantity>
, 
<specimenCount id="ECCA2ADE4131E9356835D20FFC272619" box="[879,1008,1127,1151]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
at 
<quantity id="3D344CB24131E9356F4DD20FFBA22618" box="[1047,1141,1127,1151]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
altitude). Although it has never been reared from 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356AF7D2E3FDDB26C4" box="[429,524,1163,1186]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356AF7D2E3FDDB26C4" box="[429,524,1163,1186]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this pine species is strongly indicated as the host plant of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356FE7D2E3FAF726C4" box="[1213,1312,1163,1186]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356FE7D2E3FAF726C4" box="[1213,1312,1163,1186]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to (1) evidence of the records for 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356A8AD2D8FDE626A1" box="[464,561,1200,1223]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356A8AD2D8FDE626A1" box="[464,561,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
covering the geographical and altitudinal distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356FE0D2D8FACF26A1" box="[1210,1304,1200,1223]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356FE0D2D8FACF26A1" box="[1210,1304,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and (2) the occurrence of other representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E93569DFD2BBFD30268D" authorityName=": Taeger" authorityYear="1987" box="[645,743,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpigena">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E93569DFD2BBFD30268D" box="[645,743,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">alpigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group on 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E935683ED2BBFC73268C" box="[868,932,1235,1258]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E935683ED2BBFC73268C" box="[868,932,1235,1258]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(‘ 
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356898D2BBFBC2268D" box="[962,1045,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Strobus</emphasis>
’). 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356F60D2BBFB15268C" authorityName="Turra (Liston" authorityYear="1995" box="[1082,1218,1235,1258]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mugo">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356F60D2BBFB15268C" box="[1082,1218,1235,1258]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus mugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs in the subalpine zone of the Rila and Pirin Mountains, but the restricted distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356F76D290FB5A2769" box="[1068,1165,1272,1295]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peuce">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356F76D290FB5A2769" box="[1068,1165,1272,1295]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. peuce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be explained by the far wider range of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E9356ACAD373FE3D2754" authorityName="Turra (Liston" authorityYear="1995" box="[400,490,1307,1330]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mugo">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356ACAD373FE3D2754" box="[400,490,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. mugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a member of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44131E93569A8D373FC5B2754" authority="(Pinus)" box="[754,908,1306,1330]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pinus">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E93569A8D373FCE52754" box="[754,818,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="C8B83D454131E9356818D373FC552754" box="[834,898,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pinus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
